  1052	def _apply_graph_conflict_penalty(recommendations: List[Dict[str, Any]]) -> None:
  1053	    """Increase uncertainty when conflicting skills are both recommended.
  1054	
  1055	    T-SAP-04 (R46-002): defense-in-depth reciprocity check. The compiled graph
  1056	    promises that `conflicts` pairs are mutually declared (T-SGC-03 compiler
  1057	    gate), but the runtime re-verifies by reading per-skill
  1058	    `graph-metadata.json` before penalizing. If a pair is unilateral, the
  1059	    penalty is skipped — a unilateral metadata edit must not silently
  1060	    create a bilateral runtime penalty.
