+{"type":"iteration","iteration":2,"focus":"F2 PC-005 bench","status":"evidence","newInfoRatio":0.82}
+{"type":"observation","id":"F2-O1","summary":"The bench script itself documents and enforces a required --dataset JSONL argument.","evidence":[".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_bench.py:8",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_bench.py:241"]}
+{"type":"observation","id":"F2-O2","summary":"The PC-005 playbook currently documents a bare skill_advisor_bench.py invocation and therefore omits the required --dataset flag.","evidence":[".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/10--python-compat/005-bench-runner.md:33",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/10--python-compat/005-bench-runner.md:36"]}
+{"type":"observation","id":"F2-O3","summary":"The adjacent PC-004 scenario names the checked-in regression fixture path, and the bench harness only requires each JSONL row to contain a non-empty prompt field, which that fixture does.","evidence":[".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/10--python-compat/004-regression-suite.md:35",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/10--python-compat/004-regression-suite.md:37",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_bench.py:54",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_bench.py:73"]}
+{"type":"observation","id":"F2-O4","summary":"Measured run on this machine used the checked-in regression fixture with --runs 1 and exited 1: warm p95 25.2627 ms, cold subprocess p95 876.8873 ms, throughput multiplier 37.799, gates warm=false cold=false throughput=true.","evidence":["/tmp/pc005-runs1.json:2","/tmp/pc005-runs1.json:3","/tmp/pc005-runs1.json:10","/tmp/pc005-runs1.json:21","/tmp/pc005-runs1.json:41","/tmp/pc005-runs1.json:42","/tmp/pc005-runs1.json:47"]}
+{"type":"observation","id":"F2-O5","summary":"The Python bench's warm gate default is 20 ms and cold gate default is 60 ms, while the feature catalog says the 50/60 ms design envelope is not an enforceable CI-style gate because p95 timing varies with sandbox load.","evidence":[".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_bench.py:246",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_bench.py:247",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/08--python-compat/03-bench-runner.md:21"]}
+{"type":"observation","id":"F2-O6","summary":"The TypeScript scorer latency bench on this machine reports cacheHitP95Ms 3.597 ms and uncachedP95Ms 7.086 ms with passed=true, so the native scorer path is not showing the latency regression implied by PC-005's Python cold gate failure.","evidence":[".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/bench/scorer-bench.ts:50",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/bench/scorer-bench.ts:53",".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/bench/scorer-bench.ts:61"]}
